## Quality-Diversity Search: MAP-Elites for Strategy Evolution

The EVOLUTION phase's knowledge recombination can be significantly enhanced by quality-diversity (QD) algorithms, which maintain a diverse archive of high-quality solutions indexed by behavioral characteristics. Rather than converging on a single "best" strategy, QD search produces a repertoire of diverse strategies, each optimal for a different niche.

### MAP-Elites Architecture

**Reference**: Mouret & Clune, "Illuminating search spaces by mapping elites," arXiv:1504.04909, 2015. Extended by DCRL-MAP-Elites (ACM TELO 2024, GECCO 2023 Best Paper Award).

MAP-Elites maintains a grid (or archive) indexed by behavioral descriptors. Each cell contains the highest-performing solution for that behavioral niche. New solutions are generated by mutation/crossover from existing archive members, then placed in their corresponding behavioral cell — replacing the current occupant only if they achieve higher quality.

**Reference**: Santos, Julia, do Nascimento, "Diverse Prompts: Illuminating the Prompt Space of LLMs with MAP-Elites," IEEE CEC 2025, arXiv:2504.14367. Demonstrates MAP-Elites for generating structurally diverse, high-performing prompts across seven BigBench Lite tasks.

**Reference**: Samvelyan et al., "Rainbow Teaming: Open-Ended Generation of Diverse Adversarial Prompts," NeurIPS 2024, arXiv:2402.16822. First large-scale demonstration of MAP-Elites for systematic LLM vulnerability mapping. Archive dimensions: attack style × risk category. Achieves >90% attack success across Llama 2/3 models.

### Map to Roko's EVOLUTION Phase

Instead of random pairing for knowledge recombination, MAP-Elites provides structured exploration of the strategy space:

```rust
/// MAP-Elites archive for quality-diversity strategy evolution.
/// Based on Mouret & Clune (2015), DCRL-MAP-Elites (ACM TELO 2024),
/// Rainbow Teaming (NeurIPS 2024).
pub struct MapElitesArchive {
    /// Behavioral descriptor dimensions for the archive grid.
    /// Each dimension represents a measurable behavioral characteristic.
    pub descriptor_dimensions: Vec<DescriptorDimension>,
    /// Number of bins per dimension.
    pub bins_per_dimension: usize,         // default: 10, range: 5-25
    /// Maximum archive size (total cells = bins^dimensions).
    pub max_archive_size: usize,           // default: 1000, range: 100-10000
    /// Mutation rate for generating new candidate strategies.
    pub mutation_rate: f64,                // default: 0.20, range: 0.05-0.50
    /// Whether to use HDC-based behavioral descriptors (vs. hand-designed).
    pub hdc_descriptors: bool,             // default: true
    /// Minimum quality threshold to enter the archive.
    pub min_quality_threshold: f64,        // default: 0.30, range: 0.10-0.60
}

/// A behavioral descriptor dimension for MAP-Elites indexing.
pub struct DescriptorDimension {
    /// Name of this behavioral dimension.
    pub name: String,
    /// Minimum value in this dimension.
    pub min_value: f64,
    /// Maximum value in this dimension.
    pub max_value: f64,
}

/// A cell in the MAP-Elites archive.
pub struct ArchiveCell {
    /// The strategy occupying this cell (highest quality for this niche).
    pub strategy: EvolutionaryStrategy,
    /// Quality score (fitness).
    pub quality: f64,
    /// Behavioral descriptor values (one per dimension).
    pub descriptors: Vec<f64>,
    /// Number of times this cell has been updated (replacement count).
    pub update_count: usize,
    /// When this cell was last updated.
    pub last_updated: chrono::DateTime<chrono::Utc>,
}

/// A strategy candidate in the EVOLUTION phase.
pub struct EvolutionaryStrategy {
    /// Strategy ID.
    pub id: String,
    /// Natural language description of the strategy.
    pub description: String,
    /// Parent strategy IDs (from crossover/mutation).
    pub parents: Vec<String>,
    /// HDC vector encoding of the strategy.
    pub hdc_vector: HdcVector,
    /// Fitness evaluation from BayesianMemeticFitness.
    pub fitness: FitnessEvaluation,
    /// Generation number (0 = original heuristic, N = N mutations from original).
    pub generation: usize,
}
```

### MAP-Elites EVOLUTION Algorithm

```
MAP-ELITES-EVOLUTION(archive, promoted_knowledge, config):
  // Phase 1: Initialize archive from existing promoted heuristics
  IF archive.is_empty():
    FOR heuristic in promoted_knowledge:
      descriptors = compute_behavioral_descriptors(heuristic, config)
      cell_index = discretize(descriptors, config.bins_per_dimension)
      archive.insert_if_better(cell_index, heuristic, heuristic.fitness)

  // Phase 2: Generate new candidates via mutation/crossover
  n_candidates = config.max_archive_size / 10  // 10% of archive per EVOLUTION cycle
  FOR i in 1..n_candidates:
    // Select parent(s) from archive
    parent_a = archive.random_occupied_cell().strategy
    parent_b = archive.random_occupied_cell().strategy

    // Crossover: HDC bundling of parent vectors
    child_vector = HdcVector::bundle(&[&parent_a.hdc_vector, &parent_b.hdc_vector])

    // Mutation: random bit flips proportional to mutation_rate
    child_vector = child_vector.mutate(config.mutation_rate)

    // Generate natural-language strategy description via LLM
    child_description = llm_generate_strategy(parent_a, parent_b, child_vector)

    // Evaluate fitness via BayesianMemeticFitness
    child_fitness = evaluate_fitness(child_description, recent_episodes)

    // Compute behavioral descriptors
    descriptors = compute_behavioral_descriptors(child, config)
    cell_index = discretize(descriptors, config.bins_per_dimension)

    // Insert into archive if quality exceeds current occupant
    IF child_fitness.fitness_point_estimate > config.min_quality_threshold:
      archive.insert_if_better(cell_index, child, child_fitness)

  // Phase 3: Report archive statistics
  RETURN ArchiveReport {
    filled_cells: archive.occupied_count(),
    coverage: archive.occupied_count() / archive.total_cells(),
    mean_quality: archive.mean_quality(),
    best_quality: archive.max_quality(),
    qd_score: archive.sum_quality(),  // QD-score: sum of all cell qualities
  }
```

### Test Criteria for MAP-Elites Evolution

```
1. Archive insertion: a candidate with higher quality than the current cell occupant
   replaces it; a lower-quality candidate does not.
2. Quality threshold: candidates with fitness below min_quality_threshold are never inserted.
3. Coverage growth: after 100 EVOLUTION cycles with diverse heuristics, at least 30% of
   archive cells are occupied.
4. QD-score monotonicity: QD-score (sum of all cell qualities) never decreases across
   EVOLUTION cycles (replacements only improve quality).
5. Mutation diversity: child vectors have HDC similarity to parents in range [0.4, 0.8]
   (not identical, not orthogonal).
6. Behavioral descriptor validity: descriptors for each strategy fall within the configured
   [min_value, max_value] range for each dimension.
```

